# ── Linux-only transitive deps of keyring, pinned explicitly so pip-compile
# ── captures them regardless of the compile host platform. Without this,
# ── --require-hashes install on Linux CI/Railway rejects them as unpinned
# ── transitives (keyring gates them on Linux only, so a macOS-generated
# ── lockfile omits them entirely). No platform markers here because
# ── pip-compile itself ignores markers that don't match the compile host.
# ── The cost on macOS/Windows is installing two small pure-Python wheels
# ── that keyring never calls into on those platforms — harmless.
